  "local_port": 37968,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What Pok\u00e9mon hatches from Eggs in Pok\u00e9mon GO?",
  "response": "In Pok\u00e9mon GO, **Eggs** are a core feature that allow players to hatch new Pok\u00e9mon by walking a certain distance. Eggs come in different categories based on the distance required to hatch them, and each category has its own pool of possible Pok\u00e9mon that can emerge from them. Below is an overview of the egg types, their required distances, and examples of Pok\u00e9mon that can hatch from each:\n\n### **1. 2 km Eggs**\n*These are the most common eggs and require you to walk 2 kilometers to hatch.*\n\n**Examples of Pok\u00e9mon from 2 km Eggs:**\n- **Bulbasaur** (Family)\n- **Charmander** (Family)\n- **Squirtle** (Family)\n- **Dratini**\n- **Haunter**\n- **Pangoro**\n- **Electrike** (Family)\n- **Spoink** (Family)\n- **Staryu** (Family)\n\n### **2. 5 km Eggs**\n*Requires walking 5 kilometers to hatch. Offers a wider variety of Pok\u00e9mon, including some rarer species.*\n\n**Examples of Pok\u00e9mon from 5 km Eggs:**\n- **Pidgey** (Family)\n- **Zubat** (Family)\n- **Gloom** (Family)\n- **Onix** (Family)\n- **Linoone** (Family)\n- **Vigoroth** (Family)\n- **Gligar** (Family)\n- **Sneasel** (Family)\n- **Grimer** (Family)\n\n### **3. 7 km Eggs**\n*Requires walking 7 kilometers. Contains more rare Pok\u00e9mon compared to 2 km and 5 km eggs.*\n\n**Examples of Pok\u00e9mon from 7 km Eggs:**\n- **Kadabra**\n- **Primeape** (Family)\n- **Machoke** (Family)\n- **Seviper** (Family)\n- **Arbok** (Family)\n- **Vileplume** (Family)\n- **Muk**\n- **Rhydon** (Family)\n- **Snorlax**\n\n### **4. 10 km Eggs**\n*These eggs require walking 10 kilometers and often contain some of the rarer and higher CP Pok\u00e9mon.*\n\n**Examples of Pok\u00e9mon from 10 km Eggs:**\n- **Dragonair** (Family)\n- **Hitmonlee** (Family)\n- **Hitmonchan** (Family)\n- **Lickitung**\n- **Magmar** (Family)\n- **Steelix** (Family)\n- **Rhydon**\n- **Chansey**\n\n### **5. 12 km Eggs**\n*Requires walking 12 kilometers. These eggs have an even more exclusive selection of Pok\u00e9mon.*\n\n**Examples of Pok\u00e9mon from 12 km Eggs:**\n- **Lapras** (Family)\n- **Snorlax**\n- **Gengar** (Family)\n- **Dratini** (Family)\n- **Mew** (in special events)\n  \n### **6. 14 km Eggs**\n*The rarest eggs, requiring 14 kilometers to hatch. These often contain some of the most exclusive and powerful Pok\u00e9mon.*\n\n**Examples of Pok\u00e9mon from 14 km Eggs:**\n- **Dratini** (Family)\n- **Lapras** (Family)\n- **Mew** (only available during special events)\n  \n### **Special Note on Pok\u00e9Stops and Events:**\n- **Nest Eggs:** Occasionally, specific Pok\u00e9Stops become \"nests\" for certain Pok\u00e9mon, increasing their spawn rates in that area. Eggs from these nests may have a higher chance of hatching the nest Pok\u00e9mon.\n  \n- **Event-Exclusive Eggs:** During special events, Niantic may introduce exclusive eggs or temporarily change the pool of Pok\u00e9mon available in existing egg categories.\n\n### **General Tips for Hatching Eggs:**\n1. **Use Incubators Wisely:** Each player receives one free incubator; additional incubators can be purchased. Assign incubators to higher-distance eggs first to maximize your chances of obtaining rare Pok\u00e9mon.\n2. **Walk Efficiently:** Combine egg hatching with your regular walking or commuting routine to accumulate distance faster.\n3. **Check Egg Types Regularly:** The available egg types can rotate, so check the current offerings in the Park or main screen regularly to plan your hatching strategy.\n\n### **Conclusion**\nWhile the above examples provide a snapshot of the Pok\u00e9mon that can hatch from eggs in Pok\u00e9mon GO, the actual pool is extensive and subject to change with game updates, events, and regional availability. For the most up-to-date information, consider checking the [official Pok\u00e9mon GO website](https://pokemongolive.com) or community resources like [The Silph Road](https://thesilphroad.com), which maintain comprehensive and current databases of egg hatchables.",
